The United States (US) has abandoned the Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action (JCPOA), under which the 2015 deal is implemented, and tensions are again rising in the Gulf. The EU said the July 28 extraordinary meeting would be chaired by the secretary general of the European External Action Service, Helga Maria Schmid. It said the talks were requested by Britain, France, Germany and Iran and "will examine issues linked to the implementation of the JCPOA in all its aspects." Iranian authorities had previously announced the meeting. Or Friday, amid rising hostilities between Tehran and Western capitals, Iran's Revolutionary Guards Corps seized a tanker sailing under the flag of US ally Britain. --AFP--